    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University of Leipzig</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Chronic inflammatory activation in fat tissue can be the link between adiposity and an
      increased risk for atherosclerosis. Aim of the study is to investigate how molecular
      alterations in fat tissue can be influenced by regular physical exercise training alone or in
      combination with a medical therapy (Glitazon or Metformin) in obese patients with stable CAD
      and impaired glucose tolerance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
